item.title: Mt Atkinson
item.dc:creator: kivindra
item.content:encoded:
Why Mt Atkinson?

A prime position in Truganina, just 25km west of Melbourne’s CBD, where you can escape the hustle and bustle without compromising convenience. Mt. Atkinson is a brand new community in Truganina that’s been designed to meet every aspect of quality, modern living in Melbourne’s fast-growing western corridor. Growth Potential: Truganina is experiencing rapid urban development, with new residential and commercial projects (Ex West Gate Tunnel Project). This growth potential makes it an attractive area for long-term property appreciation. West Gate Tunnel Project: The project aims to provide a vital alternative to the West Gate Bridge, reducing traffic congestion and improving travel times between Melbourne’s western suburbs and the city center. The project is estimated to cost around $10 billion, with funding coming from a mix of state government contributions and tolls from drivers using the tunnel. Originally slated for completion in 2022, the project has faced delays, with the expected completion now pushed to late 2025.

item.title: St Boulevard – Anaca
item.dc:creator: kivindra
item.content:encoded: Why St Boulevard – Magnolia? Anaca is one of three buildings of the St Boulevard which consists with other buildings named Ginko, Magnolia. ### **Universities:** 1. **University of Melbourne (Southbank Campus - Victorian College of the Arts)** Approximately 2.3 km away (6-minute drive or 25-minute walk), located in the Southbank arts precinct. 2. **Swinburne University of Technology (Prahran Campus)** Approximately 3 km away (8-minute drive), located in nearby Prahran. 3. **RMIT University (City Campus)** Approximately 3.5 km away (10-minute drive or 25-minute tram ride). 4. **Monash University (Caulfield Campus)** Approximately 6 km away (15-minute drive), located in Caulfield. 5. **Victoria University (City Flinders Campus)** Approximately 4 km away (10-minute drive), located in the Melbourne CBD. ### **Landmarks:** 1. **Albert Park Lake** Approximately 700 meters away (9-minute walk), a large recreational park famous for its lake and the Australian Grand Prix. 2. **Royal Botanic Gardens** Approximately 2 km away (5-minute drive or 20-minute walk), a popular Melbourne landmark for walking, gardens, and nature. 3. **Shrine of Remembrance** Approximately 2.2 km away (5-minute drive), a major war memorial with great views of the city. 4. **National Gallery of Victoria (NGV)** Approximately 2.7 km away (7-minute drive), one of Australia’s major art galleries located on St Kilda Road. 5. **Flinders Street Station** Approximately 3.5 km away (10-minute drive or 20-minute tram ride), one of Melbourne’s most iconic landmarks and central train stations.
